{"/service/ndnp/fu/batch_fu_bobcats_ver01/data/sn78000090/0041418067A/1949031101/0122.xml":{"full_text":"Page Twelve\nSavannah, Georgia\nENGEL'S OUTSTANDING FILMS\nBY LEON GUTTERMAN\n(Copyright, 1949, Jewish Telegraphic Agency, Inc.)\nWhen Toastmaster George Jessel last week presented to 20th-\nCentury Fox Producer Samuel G. Engel the annual Photoplay Maga\nzine gold medal, at the swankiest cinemaland affair of the year, for\nhaving produced the nation's most enjoyed motion pictures, \"Sitting\nPretty\" and \"A Street With No Name.\" according to the nation-wide\nyear-long election conducted by the magazine among America's\nmovie-goers. Producer Engel found himself sitting pretty solidly on\ntop of the movie world 'ladder\u2014the result of intelligence, talent,\nability and many years of hard work.\nBut what made many Filmland\ncitizens so proud of Engel\u2019s win\nning this honor was the fact that\nthis extremely well-liked, uni\nquely popular motion-picture\ncreative artist was also a man\n.loved and admired by the people\nPURIM GREETINGS!\nCOAL\nIN BAGS ORTONS\nGuaranteed\nQuality\nJoseph F. Griffin\nFUEL SUPPLY CO.\nPHONE 2-2165\nPURIM GREETINGS\nPT A7A\nRESTAURANT\n12 W. BROUGHTON ST.\nSAVANNAH, GEORGIA\nGREETINGS AND BEST WISHES\nROWLAND INSURANCE and\nREAL ESTATE AGENCY, Inc.\nHARRY PALMER LOUISE YARBROUGH\n18 East Bryan Street Phone 3-5183\nSAVANNAH, GEORGIA\nPURIM GREETINGS AND BEST WISHES\nCOASTAL PROPERTIES\nPlantation Estates Farms Timber lands\nWaterfront Homes\nR. L. T. R. COOPER\nREALTORS\nCitizens Trust Building Phone 3-1271\nPURIM GREETINGS\nPeoples Hardware Co.\n125 AND .127 CONGRESS STREET. WEST\nSAVANNAH, GEORGIA\nBEST WISHES to OTTR many FRIENDS\nL. C. KESSLER CO.\nELECTRIC CONTRACTOR\n35 Years Experience\nWIRING FIXTURES REPAIRS\n1515 Paulsen Street Dial 3-7528 3-3415 5022\nPURIM GREETINGS AND BEST WISHES\nGOODYEAR SERVICE\nPERRY AT DRAYTON\nPHONE 8163\nPURIM GREETINGS AND BEST WISHES\nACOUSTICON\nNow at new low orire! With ell the famous\nScientific fittina service!\nBATTERIES FOR ALL MAKES OF HEARING AIDS\nACOUSTICON ELLIOTT CO.\nT. G. ELLIOTT\n26 East Broughton Street\nPhone 2-1000 Savannah, Ga.\nof his own faith for his great\nknowledge of Hebrew and his\nearnest efforts to spread the wis\ndom of the Torah to as many as\nwill listen.\nFor Sam Engel is profoundly\na religious man \u2014a deep student\nof the philosophy of life who\nnever loses a wisp of faith\nin either God or man, or the im\nperfectability of a universe of\nrighteousness which they can\nfashion together. He sees in hu\nmanity and motion pictures a po\ntential partnership and has set\nabout to break down first the\ndownright hostility, then the\nshyness and diffidence which hu\nman culture and motion pictures\nfeel in each other\u2019s presence.\nThat his message of better pic\nture making is spreading Holly\nwood has reason to believe from\nthe increasing hordes who flock\nto his films the world over.\n\u201cHollywood producers must be\nleaders of ideas,\u201d Engel believes.\n\u201cThe temporary film is still fru\nstrated in many ways. Few studios\nwish to expend money attempt\ning new dramatic forms, giving\nnew young talent a break. Stag\nnation results. This lack of pos\nsibility of greater freedom of\nproduction reduces the desire of\nyoung writers and of those who\nTHE SOUTHERN JEWISH WEEKLY\nhave talent coupled with am\nbition. Thus if we don\u2019t change\nour particular ideology of op\nportunity soon, we are going to\nwitness the peculiar phenomenon\nof the growth of a new genera\ntion without the possibility of\nexpressing itself. Hollywood\nmust not remain tied to old and\nrepetitive forms simply because\nthe industry runs under a profit\nand loss system. There must be\nsincere regard for the audience.\u201d\nEngel feels that the progress\nof the motion picture must be in\nthe direction of mass expression.\nIt can no longer remain aloof\nlike an expensive plaything. It\nmust be used for experimenta\ntion of new forms, it must be the\nlaboratory through which is pic\ntured, with skill and honesty, the\never-changing forces of world\nmovements. It cannot remain\naloof. This aloofness has been\nresponsible for much of the mo\nvie box-office recession.\nSam Engel\u2019s own mind is not\nmerely a storehouse, it is a stu\ndio, a laboratory, a forge in\nwhich a creative artist burns out\nthe dross of conflict and confus\nion, enabling his fellowmen to\nfashion new hope in their per\nsonal lives through the motion\npicture insight he gives them.\nHis reading is lightning swift, his\nunderstanding encyclopedic, his\nmemory a photographic process\nwhich preserves every bit of\nmeaping and files away, cata\nlogued and ready for use, a nev\ner-failing reservoir of ideas and\ninformation.\n$2,000,000 For\nCyprus Camps\nLondon (ZOA) The sum of\nL. 500,000 ($2,000,000) was spent\nby Great Britain on maintaining\nthe Refugee Camps on Cyprus\nfrom May 15th to the end of No\nvember 1948.\nPURIM GREETINGS\nSewing Machines Rentals\nParts Repairs\nSewing Service\nSupplies\n15 EAST YORK STREET\nSAVANNAH, GEORGIA\nPHONE 3-8014\nPAUL S. MOON, Mgr.\nButtons Buckles Belts\nHemstitching Button Holes\nBEST WISHES\nSchwanebeck's\nSavannah's Historical\nPink House\n25 Abercorn Street\nCHURCH and SUNDAY\nSCHOOL SUPPLIES\nTelephone 7245\nBEST WISHES\nv\nW. T.\nGRANT CO.\nSAVANNAH. GEORGIA\n\"The Coastal Empire\"\nPreparing for Festival of Purim\nla the Beth Zeiroth Mizrachi\ng IpL }w\nHUH WsBISm\nA student at the Beth Zeiroth Mizrachi in Jerusalem puts the\nfinishing touches on a puppet in preparation for a Purim play\nbeing given at the girls vocational training school, one of 47\nprojects sponsored in Israel by the Mizrachi Women\u2019s Organiza\ntion of America. Although the Beth Zeiroth Mizrachi was estab\nlished for the training of adolescent girls, the building is now also\nhousing younger children who have recently arrived in Israel,\nuntil additional facilities are made available through the Mizrachi\nWomen\u2019s expansion program.\nGREETINGS AND BEST WISHES\nCINDERELLA SHOP\n245 BULL STREET PHONE 3-0279\nSAVANNAH\u2019S ONLY SHOP EXCLUSIVELY FOR GIRLS\nINFANCY TO 14 YEARS\nPURIM GREETINGS AND BEST WISHES\nSHEPHERD BROS.. INC.\nWINDOW SHADES VENETIAN BLINDS\nSPECIALIST\nPhone 3-2096 2426 Abercorn Street\nPurim Greetings end Best Wishes To All\nLIBERTT BICYCLE STORE\nA. J. SWAIN\nBICYCLES TOYS RADIOS AUTO TIRES\nEASY terms\n308 West Liberty St\u2014SAVANNAH, GA. Phone 2-3525\nPurim Greetings and Best Wishes To All\n'TOR SHOW CARDS THAT ARE SMART\"\nTHE ART MART\nARTIST. B. M. NASH\n4 COMMERCIAL PERSONAL\n\u2014147 Drayton Street Savannah. Ga.\nPurim Greetings and Best Wishes To All\nDADH COMPANY, Inc.\nGEORGE F. DAUM\nPhono a Distributors PHILCO Products\nPhone 4-2409 410 E< B ay street\nSAVANNAH. GEORGIA\nGREETINGS AND BEST WISHES\nStubbs Hardware Company\nINCORPORATED\n,oo SPORTING GOODS\n123 Congress Street SAVANNAH, GA Telephone 5149\nPURIM GREETINGS\nGREENO REALTY CO.\nMember ofSavannah, Realtors Association\nInvestment Gold Mining Properties\n192 EAST Homes W*ter Front Sit\u00ae*\nlast BRYAN STREET SAVANNAH. GA\u00bb__\nFriday, March 11, 1949","height":"25548","width":"16095"}}
